{"TopicId":212039,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"How is the lower orbit of each planet determined?","CreatedByName":"tim233","CreatedById":225536,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-15T11:20:36Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"tim233","CreatedById":225536,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-15T11:20:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is a mission to fly by the sun but i do not know how to achieve the most fuel savings\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"James Kerman","CreatedById":160462,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-15T11:35:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWelcome to the forum \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/225536-tim233/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022225536\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/225536-tim233/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@tim233\u003C/a\u003E!\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:happy:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/happy.png\u0022 title=\u0022:happy:\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYour question has been moved from KSP Discussion to gameplay questions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Leganeski","CreatedById":220954,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-15T16:33:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you need to do something while in \u0022space just above the sun\u0022, then that means below an altitude of 1,000,000 km.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"king of nowhere","CreatedById":204876,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-15T17:43:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224232415\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022212039\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221676460036\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022225536\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tim233\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, tim233 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is a mission to fly by the sun but i do not know how to achieve the most fuel savings\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nif your mission is to achieve a \u0022fly-by\u0022, then you only need to exit the sphere of influence of kerbin.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darthgently","CreatedById":204885,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-15T18:18:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224232415\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022212039\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221676460036\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022225536\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tim233\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, tim233 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is a mission to fly by the sun but i do not know how to achieve the most fuel savings\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter some trial and error, my method of getting to solar orbit and back with the least \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003EDV\u003C/abbr\u003E is that you want your solar orbit velocity to be close to Kerbin\u0027s solar orbit velocity upon exiting Kerbin\u0027s \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0 This will minimize \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003EDV\u003C/abbr\u003E to return back into Kerbin\u0027s \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t forget to linger in Solar orbit long enough to satisfy the contract.\u00A0 Usually 10 game seconds or so\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}